  "bib_entries": {
    "37941491": {
      "title": "Defining 'surveillance' in drug safety",
      "abstract": "The concept of surveillance in pharmacovigilance and pharmacoepidemiology has evolved from the concept of surveillance in epidemiology, particularly of infectious diseases. We have surveyed the etymology, usages, and previous definitions of ‘surveillance’ and its modifiers, such as ‘active’ and ‘passive’."
    }
